items.description: This project analyzes 2,512 financial transaction records using unsupervised learning to identify natural behavior clusters. By applying K-Means and the Elbow Method, it reveals distinct transaction patterns, detects potential fraud, and provides insights to improve financial security and anomaly monitoring.
